wc command
Gives the byte, line, character and word count for given file.
i.e. wc file.txt
Above will state respective counts for text within the file.

wc -c (byte count)
wc -l (line count)
wc -m (character count)
wc -w (word count)
Specific commands only call respective counts.
i.e. wc -w file.txt
Above gives word count only of text within the file.

The command can be applied to results passed to it via pipe redirection.
i.e. env | grep ^T | wc -l
Above counts lines of results (i.e. number of results) of a list of environmental variables that begin with capital letter T.
